The paper deals with compressed self-indexes for text data, which is a topic closely related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). It also involves dictionary compression, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes a new universal compressed self-index, which involves designing efficient algorithms and data structures (cs.CC). The paper also involves analyzing the space and time complexity of the proposed index, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CR).
